    "comment": "Rationale: Plekhg5 is a GEF that regulates the activity of Rab26 (Fig 7). In axons, loss of Plekhg5 led to a reduction in autophagosome density that could be elevated by expression of Rab26QL. Additionally, loss of the GEF also increases levels of the synaptic vesicle markers (synaptophysin 1, synaptobrevin 1, synaptotagmin 1 and synapsin 1). This is indicative that Rab26 and its GEF is involved in the degradation of synaptic vesicle proteins via autophagy.\n\nUniprot: has lipid anchor. Experimental description: - \"To generate Plekhg5-deficient mice....\"",
